       ccaalleennddaarr..ooffffsseett==00
              If "1" the first month in the calendar report is effectively changed by the offset value specified in calendar.offset.value. It defaults to "0".

       ccaalleennddaarr..ooffffsseett..vvaalluuee==--11
              The offset value to apply to the first month in the calendar report. The default value is "-1".

       ccaalleennddaarr..hhoolliiddaayyss==nnoonnee
              If  set to full running "task calendar" will display holidays in the calendar by color-coding the corresponding days. A detailed list with the dates and names of the holi‐
              days is also shown. If set to sparse only the days are color-coded and no details on the holidays will be displayed. The displaying of holidays is turned  off  by  setting
              the variable to none. The default value is "none".

       ccaalleennddaarr..lleeggeenndd==11
              Determines whether the calendar legend is displayed. The default value is "1".

       ccaalleennddaarr..mmoonntthhssppeerrlliinnee==NN
